By @VargaJoe

```csharp
var crmcontactsall = this.Model.Items.Where(c => c.Type("RorWebCRMContact") && c.Path.StartsWith(company.Path)).ToList();
```

This worked in 7.0.2, but after upgrading to 7.1.1 it gives _0 results_ without an error. If we replace the 'startswith' term with 'InTree' (which is the recommended way anyway) it works correctly.

```csharp
var crmcontactsall = this.Model.Items.Where(c => c.Type("RorWebCRMContact") && c.InTree(company.Path)).ToList();
```

@kavics: Has something changed related to this feature in the last few releases? Should this work?
@VargaJoe: please clarify the type of _Model.Items_, is that a list in a collection view (ascx)?
